@namespace DotNetCloud.Modules.Bookmarks.UI

@*
    Help content for the Bookmarks module.
*@

<div class="help-content">
    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Overview</h2>
        <p>DotNetCloud Bookmarks lets you save, organize, and search web links. Keep your favorite pages organized in folders with tags for easy retrieval.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Adding Bookmarks</h2>
        <p><strong>Adding a bookmark:</strong> Click <strong>New Bookmark</strong> and enter the URL, title, and optionally select a folder or add tags. The page metadata (title, description, favicon) is fetched automatically.</p>
        <p><strong>Browser extension:</strong> Use the DotNetCloud browser extension to save bookmarks directly from your browser.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Organizing Bookmarks</h2>
        <p><strong>Folders:</strong> Create folders in the sidebar to group bookmarks by category (e.g., "Work", "Reading", "Reference").</p>
        <p><strong>Tags:</strong> Add tags to bookmarks for cross-folder categorization. Filter by tag to find related bookmarks quickly.</p>
        <p><strong>Favorites:</strong> Star important bookmarks for quick access.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Searching Bookmarks</h2>
        <p>Use the search bar to find bookmarks by title, URL, or tags. Results update as you type.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Importing &amp; Exporting</h2>
        <p>Import bookmarks from browser HTML export files (standard bookmarks.html format). Export your bookmarks as HTML for backup or migration.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Tips &amp; Tricks</h2>
        <ul class="help-tips">
            <li>Use folders for broad categories and tags for cross-cutting topics.</li>
            <li>Check your bookmarks periodically to remove broken links.</li>
            <li>Use the browser extension for quick saving while browsing.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</div>
